item.title: Unreachable statement
item.dc:creator: @Aurai Aurai
item.description:
@Aurai wrote:

surfer25:

try taking out the last } above it

No, that closes the else if statement above the break.
Try placing the break under the end of your switch(objcetID) { } statement.
If you send me your client, I can fix it for you. You placed a break before your objectID switch, but the objectID integer is defined in the 132 packetType case, and you’re ending the case before your objectID switch, so not only does the code become unreachable, you will also get errors stating that the compiler is unable to find the objectID integer (it won’t show it now, because you have an unreachable statement).

First, try removing the break statement

break;

all together. If that doesn’t work, then place it at the bottom of your objectID switch.
